title: Desperate Gazans scramble for aid truck water supplies
description: Video from Khan Younis shows internally displaced Gazans mobbing Egyptian aid trucks filled with bottled water. The United Nations has said that water shortages have “become a matter of life and death” in the besieged territory.

title: North Korea launches suspected spy satellite, its neighbors say
description: North Korea made what appeared to be its third attempt to launch its first spy satellite into orbit on Tuesday, South Korea and Japan said.

title: What the tentative Israel-Hamas hostage deal could look like
description: A deal between Israel and Hamas to release hostages and pause fighting is close to being finalized, pending approval from the Israeli government. NBC News’ Gabe Gutierrez reports on the details of the agreement that could include a hostage-prisoner swap, a pause in fighting for multiple days and allowing more humanitarian aid into Gaza.

title: Taylor Swift’s Rio tour marred by deaths, muggings and a dangerous heat wave
description: Taylor Swift's three-day leg of her eras tour in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil was marred by the deaths of two people, extreme heat and muggings and crime, as fans decried on social media.

title: Tentative deal reached to release hostages held by Hamas
description: A senior U.S. official and a source familiar with the talks tell NBC News that a tentative deal has been reached to release some hostages held by Hamas. NBC’s Keir Simmons reports for TODAY.

title: She's a world champion flag football quarterback — and she's flagging sports pay gap
description: Mexican Diana Flores, world champion flag football quarterback and NFL ambassador, points out the existing pay gap in sports and is featured in PBS's "Groundbreakers."

title: Israeli military release video showing battles in northern Gaza
description: The Israeli military released video showing fierce fighting with Palestinian militants in Jabaliya, an urban area in northern Gaza. NBC News cannot independently verify the footage, but the Israeli Defense Forces say 66 Israeli soldiers have been killed in the Gaza ground operations.

title: Houthi video shows gunmen seizing an Israeli-linked cargo ship in the Red Sea
description: Yemen’s Iran-backed Houthi rebels released a video on Monday that was said to show their forces seizing an Israeli-linked cargo ship in the Red Sea.

title: Israeli military video said to show strikes on Hezbollah targets inside Lebanon
description: The Israeli military released video on Monday that it  said showed strikes on buildings in Lebanon that it believed are linked to the Hezbollah militant group.

title: First video shows trapped tunnel workers in India
description: Rescuers on Tuesday released video of construction workers who have been trapped in a tunnel for more than a week in northern India.

title: Hundreds of Rohingya refugees arrived by boat to Indonesia in a week
description: Officials say hundreds of Rohingya Muslims arrived by boat from Myanmar to the Indonesian province of Aceh within one week. One group of about 240 people was denied twice by residents in the Aceh Utara district.

title: Argentina elects Javier Milei as new president after polarizing election
description: After a polarizing election, right-wing economist and TV personality Javier Milei won the presidential race in Argentina after a heated runoff with economy minister Sergio Massa. The nation has been plagued by soaring inflation, an issue Milei campaigned on and promised to tackle once in office. NBC News’ Steven Romo takes a look into Milei’s plans for the country’s future.

title: Meet Javier Milei, Argentina’s next president
description: Who is Javier Milei, Argentina’s president elect? The first libertarian head of state ever elected plans to reconstruct the country’s government.
